The course analyzes the principles of the circular economy, introduces the accompanying legislation, gives an overview of the planning and implementation of environmental technological processes of organizations based on the concept of sustainable development. The basics of the organisation's environmental management related to the renovation of existing technologies and the introduction of new modern technologies in the production and service spheres are discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction of the principles of the circular economy and evaluation criteria, analyzing the views of sustainable development. To analyze the organization's environmental performance based on both production technology and product handling.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has completed the course: - knows the criteria for assessing the sustainability and environmental impact of products and technologies; - knows the basic principles of the circular economy and analyzes the possibilities of waste recovery; - is able to assess the life cycle of products and point out its significant environmental problems; - is able to analyze the organisation's environmental performance and identify opportunities to improve its environmental performance.
